04:06.077 --> 04:09.080
(blender whirring loudly)

04:09.081 --> 04:14.019
(blender pulsing loudly)

04:14.020 --> 04:15.420
(relieved sigh)

04:15.421 --> 04:17.678
- (blender whirring)
- Will you stop with the blender?

04:17.678 --> 04:18.690
Sorry.

04:18.690 --> 04:20.559
I'm making Emily's welcome home dinner.

04:20.560 --> 04:22.581
I thought Emily wasn't
coming home till tomorrow.

04:25.864 --> 04:28.300
A romantic dinner requires preparation.

04:28.301 --> 04:31.770
And now if you'll excuse me,
I have to tenderize my goose.

04:31.771 --> 04:34.104
You won't have to do that
when Emily gets back.

04:36.741 --> 04:39.644
Why does everybody hate high-fives?

04:39.645 --> 04:41.078
(faint shouting)

04:43.882 --> 04:45.116
Dani, what are you doing?

04:45.117 --> 04:46.518
Storing my stuff here.

04:46.519 --> 04:47.719
Now that Emily's coming back,

04:47.720 --> 04:49.023
I have to clear out of her place

04:49.024 --> 04:50.388
and find myself an apartment.

04:50.389 --> 04:51.489
What about your apartment?

04:51.490 --> 04:52.657
I can't go back there,

04:52.658 --> 04:54.219
with the high rent and the bad plumbing

04:54.220 --> 04:55.803
and the creepy neighbor who spies on me

04:55.804 --> 04:57.978
through the bullet hole in the wall.

05:00.177 --> 05:02.334
Well, I'm sure you'll
find someplace great.

05:02.335 --> 05:04.002
Not as good as Emily's,

05:04.003 --> 05:05.971
with the free cable
and the clear water,

05:05.972 --> 05:08.605
and is no one concerned
about the bullet hole?

05:11.943 --> 05:14.244
Well, if you'll excuse me,
I have to glaze my strudel.

05:15.991 --> 05:18.482
He won't have to do that
when Emily gets back.

05:21.586 --> 05:23.754
I believe you're on the clock.

05:26.244 --> 05:27.325
- Hi, Dani.
- Hi, Charlotte.

05:27.326 --> 05:28.326
I'm off to work.

05:28.327 --> 05:29.167
I'll see you tonight?

05:29.168 --> 05:30.191
I'll pick you up at 8:00.

05:30.192 --> 05:30.929
Ooh, big plans?

05:30.930 --> 05:32.497
Yes, a little birdie reminded me

05:32.498 --> 05:34.232
that it's our three-month anniversary.

05:34.233 --> 05:36.034
So that birdie's
boyfriend is taking her

05:36.035 --> 05:37.636
to a romantic dinner.

05:37.637 --> 05:40.304
Yes, they're going to be
the cutest couple at Langford's.

05:41.706 --> 05:42.940
Langford's?

05:44.342 --> 05:46.344
The sports bar where
we go all the time?

05:46.345 --> 05:47.679
Where you're so comfortable,

05:47.680 --> 05:50.882
you've literally worn pajama bottoms?

05:50.883 --> 05:53.218
You're saying good things,

05:53.219 --> 05:56.487
but in a tone that makes me feel shame.

05:57.622 --> 06:00.725
I just assumed we were
going someplace special,

06:00.726 --> 06:03.361
given the occasion,
but Langford's is fine.

06:03.362 --> 06:04.896
That's right, I mean, let's face it,

06:04.897 --> 06:06.798
we've only been going
out for three months,

06:06.799 --> 06:09.393
and at our age, three months
goes by in, like, a day.

06:11.202 --> 06:12.037
"Our age"?

06:12.038 --> 06:13.571
My age.

06:13.572 --> 06:15.240
Not our age.

06:15.241 --> 06:16.641
I was just thinking that for me,

06:16.642 --> 06:19.843
time goes by really fast,
except for now.

06:21.579 --> 06:23.480
Which feels like forever.

06:24.516 --> 06:27.918
This is how walls get bullet holes.

06:29.054 --> 06:30.588
I will see you tonight.

06:30.589 --> 06:33.491
Why don't you wear your fancy pajamas?

06:33.492 --> 06:34.992
Ooh, the one with the feet!

06:37.228 --> 06:44.102
(video call ringtone)

06:44.103 --> 06:47.339
Emily, what a surprise.

06:47.340 --> 06:49.040
I should warn you,
if this is a booty call,

06:49.041 --> 06:50.742
we are not alone.

06:50.743 --> 06:52.077
Ugh.

06:52.078 --> 06:54.346
<i>I'm calling because
I have some great news.</i>

06:54.347 --> 06:55.547
Well, at least I think it's great,

06:55.548 --> 06:56.715
and I hope that you do too.

06:56.716 --> 06:58.049
<i>I'm sure I will... what is it?</i>

06:58.050 --> 06:59.184
Well, Fergus just called.

06:59.185 --> 07:00.251
Of course he did!

07:00.252 --> 07:02.153
He calls you all the time!

07:02.154 --> 07:04.422
And he's so happy with
what I've been doing

07:04.423 --> 07:06.057
that he asked me to help him

07:06.058 --> 07:07.759
at the big jewelry show in Paris.

07:07.760 --> 07:08.994
<i>And that's tonight?</i>

07:08.995 --> 07:13.631
No, it's in three weeks, so...

07:13.632 --> 07:15.432
I'd be home in a month.

07:18.303 --> 07:20.572
Damn it, the screen froze.

07:20.573 --> 07:21.972
Felix?

07:23.174 --> 07:24.274
<i>Screen didn't freeze.</i>

07:26.044 --> 07:27.579
<i>He's just in shock.</i>

07:27.580 --> 07:29.280
<i>Right, Felix?</i>

07:29.281 --> 07:31.483
Oh, wow.

07:31.484 --> 07:32.917
Wow, another month.

07:32.918 --> 07:33.918
Whoo!

07:33.919 --> 07:35.152
Exciting news, though.

07:35.728 --> 07:37.790
Hey listen, don't you worry
about your apartment.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.352
I will get your mail,
water your plants,

07:39.353 --> 07:40.736
and upgrade your cable to premium.

07:40.737 --> 07:42.867
<i>The Walking Dead</i> is coming back!

07:52.307 --> 07:53.777
You know, I was kind of disappointed

07:53.778 --> 07:55.045
in that tapas restaurant.

07:55.046 --> 07:58.548
Is that because you
thought I said "topless"?

07:58.549 --> 07:59.883
No!

07:59.884 --> 08:01.383
Yes.

08:03.653 --> 08:05.622
Actually, let's go to your place.

08:05.623 --> 08:07.391
Why aren't we going in?

08:07.392 --> 08:08.225
It's Felix.

08:08.226 --> 08:09.493
He's moping over Emily.

08:09.494 --> 08:11.395
I can ignore him,
but you'll get sucked in.

08:11.396 --> 08:12.796
You've got a girl heart.

08:12.797 --> 08:13.897
Emily?

08:13.898 --> 08:14.965
Oh, sorry.

08:14.966 --> 08:16.400
I heard a woman's voice

08:16.401 --> 08:18.934
and thought I might
have a reason to live.

08:21.071 --> 08:22.072
Phew!

08:22.073 --> 08:22.973
That was a close one.

08:22.974 --> 08:23.906
Let's go.

08:26.009 --> 08:28.144
Girl heart.

08:29.513 --> 08:30.781
Felix,

08:30.782 --> 08:31.882
what are you doing?

08:31.883 --> 08:33.250
Just because Emily can't be here

08:33.251 --> 08:35.315
is no reason to let this
delicious meal go to waste.

08:35.316 --> 08:36.285
I thought I could use it

08:36.287 --> 08:38.570
to plug the empty hole
where my heart used to be.

08:41.323 --> 08:42.558
Plug away, pal!

08:42.559 --> 08:43.626
Charlotte, let's go!

08:43.628 --> 08:45.462
Oscar!

08:45.463 --> 08:47.064
We can't leave him alone like this.

08:47.065 --> 08:48.131
He's in pain.

08:48.132 --> 08:49.800
I wish I were in pain.

08:49.801 --> 08:51.834
That would mean I could still feel.

08:53.270 --> 08:54.137
Here we go.

08:54.138 --> 08:55.539
Oscar!

08:55.540 --> 08:56.807
We're staying.

08:56.808 --> 08:57.841
Wonderful.

08:57.842 --> 08:59.209
Help yourselves to goose.

08:59.210 --> 09:00.677
I will grab some extra plates.

09:00.678 --> 09:03.712
And yes, Oscar, your Batman fork.

09:05.549 --> 09:07.017
How can you be so callous?

09:07.018 --> 09:08.418
I'm just sick of it.

09:08.419 --> 09:10.620
He's been wallowing over
Emily for three months now.

09:10.621 --> 09:11.688
He's a wallower,

09:11.689 --> 09:15.058
and I will no longer
swallow that wallow.

09:15.059 --> 09:16.426
He's a romantic.

09:16.427 --> 09:18.962
Not that I'd expect you to understand.

09:18.963 --> 09:21.298
What's that supposed to mean?

09:21.299 --> 09:22.962
I was afraid you were
going to abandon me,

09:22.963 --> 09:24.734
like so many others.

09:24.735 --> 09:25.836
Thank you for being here.

09:25.837 --> 09:28.871
Well, the vote was a tie.

09:29.873 --> 09:31.141
CHARLOTTE: Felix,

09:31.142 --> 09:33.210
have you told Emily how upset you are?

09:33.211 --> 09:35.786
Oh yes, and show her that I'm
the neediest man in the world?

09:35.787 --> 09:36.580
Women love that.

09:36.581 --> 09:38.715
You need to tell her how you feel.

09:38.716 --> 09:41.184
It's just so hard to talk about
feelings over the computer.

09:41.185 --> 09:43.386
Have you thought
about flying to London?

09:43.387 --> 09:45.301
Talking to her in person?

09:45.302 --> 09:46.469
What? That's insane.

09:46.470 --> 09:47.603
Who does that?

09:47.604 --> 09:48.805
Oh, I don't know,

09:48.806 --> 09:51.073
someone with romance in his soul?

09:51.074 --> 09:54.010
Who's never heard of a telephone.

09:54.011 --> 09:55.511
That's a great idea.

09:55.512 --> 09:57.480
I could fly out tomorrow morning,

09:57.481 --> 10:00.183
surprise her, take her in my arms,

10:00.184 --> 10:02.050
and kiss her enthusiastically
on the mouth.

10:03.085 --> 10:04.821
I can do this.

10:04.822 --> 10:06.255
I mean, I'm terrified of flying,

10:06.256 --> 10:08.958
but I'm more terrified of
another month without Emily.

10:08.959 --> 10:09.959
I'm going!

10:09.960 --> 10:11.543
Should I pack the goose or carry it on?

10:11.544 --> 10:13.449
You know what,
they have geese in England!

10:14.664 --> 10:17.266
I'll have you know I can
be pretty damn romantic.

10:17.267 --> 10:18.668
Remember last night,

10:18.669 --> 10:20.412
when we shared that
milkshake at Langford's?

10:20.413 --> 10:22.004
It was your third one.

10:22.005 --> 10:24.073
You couldn't finish it,
so you pushed it over to me

10:24.074 --> 10:27.009
and said you had to
unbutton your pants.

10:27.010 --> 10:30.378
And that is why I wear pajama bottoms.

10:35.718 --> 10:37.720
Thanks for helping me plan my date.

10:37.721 --> 10:40.122
I really want Charlotte to
know that I'm a romantic guy.

10:40.123 --> 10:41.190
You got it.

10:41.191 --> 10:42.625
I'm your agent...

10:42.626 --> 10:45.027
...of love.

10:45.028 --> 10:47.563
Here's what I got so far:
put on a suit...

10:47.564 --> 10:48.498
One that fits.

10:48.499 --> 10:49.464
Good, that's good.

10:50.700 --> 10:52.568
Then a carriage ride through the park,

10:52.569 --> 10:53.836
followed by dinner...

10:53.837 --> 10:56.506
At a place that doesn't
serve curly fries.

10:56.507 --> 10:58.607
Damn it, Teddy, you're on fire!

11:00.576 --> 11:02.612
Yeah!

11:02.613 --> 11:05.915
Then we come back here,
I put on a little mood music...

11:05.916 --> 11:07.483
she loves her Boyz II Men.

11:07.484 --> 11:09.252
That's one classy lady.

11:09.253 --> 11:12.087
Then I'll light some candles
and wow her with...

11:13.222 --> 11:14.490
Oh, Oscar, I'm flattered,

11:14.491 --> 11:18.160
but I think my wife might
have a problem with that.

11:18.161 --> 11:19.078
No, not that!

11:19.079 --> 11:21.199
I need you to help me come
up with some grand gesture.

11:21.200 --> 11:22.584
Something that will show Charlotte

11:22.585 --> 11:23.933
that I have romance in my soul.

11:23.934 --> 11:26.769
If only I had a way of
knowing what women think,

11:26.770 --> 11:28.404
what goes on in their brains.

11:28.405 --> 11:29.388
Well, you know, Oscar...

11:29.389 --> 11:31.641
Not now, Dani!

11:31.642 --> 11:34.075
Now I don't feel so bad
about taking your toaster.

11:36.012 --> 11:37.747
Why does this have to be so hard?

11:37.748 --> 11:39.592
Charlotte and I have been
going out for three months.

11:39.593 --> 11:40.679
I thought we were way past

11:40.680 --> 11:42.685
this whole having-to-prove-
yourself thing.

11:42.686 --> 11:44.687
(laughing)

11:44.688 --> 11:48.190
Oh, you poor, magnificent man-child.

11:48.191 --> 11:49.574
I've been married almost 20 years,

11:49.575 --> 11:50.626
and let me tell you,

11:50.627 --> 11:52.428
you always have to
keep proving yourself.

11:52.429 --> 11:53.529
- Seriously?
- Yes.

11:53.530 --> 11:56.098
Women need to feel
loved and appreciated.

11:56.099 --> 12:00.169
"Romance" is just a fancy word
for showing you give a crap.

12:00.170 --> 12:01.938
Damn.

12:01.939 --> 12:04.039
You should give a seminar.

12:06.042 --> 12:08.711
I'll make some calls
and see if I can come up

12:08.712 --> 12:10.546
with a romantic surprise for tonight.

12:10.547 --> 12:12.114
Thanks, Teddy.

12:12.115 --> 12:16.017
"Give... a... crap."

12:18.521 --> 12:21.023
Well, I'm off to the airport.

12:21.024 --> 12:22.992
Quick question:

12:22.993 --> 12:24.726
do you know where my arm is?

12:26.729 --> 12:29.164
Maybe you packed it in your suitcase?

12:31.200 --> 12:32.500
Aha!

12:33.769 --> 12:35.071
What's going on?

12:35.072 --> 12:38.140
Hm? Oh, maybe it was
those pills that you gave me.

12:38.141 --> 12:39.542
The sleeping pills?

12:39.543 --> 12:41.210
I told you to take those at the airport

12:41.211 --> 12:42.878
so you wouldn't freak out on the plane!

12:42.879 --> 12:44.080
I took them early

12:44.081 --> 12:46.748
so that I would not
freak out in the Uber.

12:48.050 --> 12:49.385
I'll be all right.

12:49.386 --> 12:51.986
Oh, look, this monkey wants
me to take a nap with him.

12:54.323 --> 12:55.958
Felix, come on!

12:55.959 --> 12:57.627
You're going to miss your plane.

12:57.628 --> 12:59.128
No, no, can't do that.

12:59.129 --> 13:02.263
Must show Emily that she's
worth crossing an ocean for.

13:07.136 --> 13:09.238
I'm not going to make it!

13:09.239 --> 13:12.141
Tell Emily I love her
more than life itself!

13:12.142 --> 13:14.210
I'm not going to England.

13:14.211 --> 13:15.610
I was talking to the monkey.

13:17.580 --> 13:20.516
Felix, I hate seeing
you torn up like this.

13:20.517 --> 13:21.683
(knock at door)

13:26.522 --> 13:28.724
Somebody call a car for the airport?

13:28.725 --> 13:30.059
Felix, come on!

13:30.060 --> 13:32.627
You gotta get up and
tell Emily how you feel!

13:34.830 --> 13:37.065
So nobody's going to the airport?

13:39.235 --> 13:40.770
You know what?

13:40.771 --> 13:43.239
I guess I am.

13:43.240 --> 13:45.841
Just get some ticket money...

13:45.842 --> 13:48.409
Ooh, I'm gonna be flying first class!

13:57.135 --> 14:00.003
